"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE1\">Alarm Config</li>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE1\">Universe Update Installer</li></ul>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"Apache Tomcat is used to run the following ENIQ Events applications:</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"\n" +
"<ul>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE0\">AdminUI</li></ul>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"The following sections describe:</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"\n" +
"<ul>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE0\">Configuring HTTPS on Apache Tomcat</li>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE1\">Importing CA (certificate authority) signed certificates</li>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE1\">Enabling and disabling HTTPS</li></ul>\n" +
"<dl class=\"note\"><dt><b>Note: &nbsp;</b></dt><dd>HTTPS is enabled by default on the ENIQ Apache Tomcat server.</dd></dl><br />\n" +
"\n"+
"</div>\n";

var C4_1_1=
"<div id=\"content\" class=\"body-content\">\n"+
"<h3><a name=\"ApacheTomcatEniqInstallation\"></a><span class=\"CHAPNUMBER\">4.1.1 &nbsp; </span><span class=\"CHAPTITLE\"><a name=\"id_2lzv\"></a><a name=\"CHAPTER4.1.1\" href='javascript:parent.parent.sC2(\"TOP\")' class=\"CHAPLINK\">Configuring Apache Tomcat during ENIQ Installation</a></span></h3>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"This section describes how Apache Tomcat is configured for HTTPS\n" +
"during the installation of ENIQ.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"\n" +
"<ol class=\"STEPLIST\"><li class=\"STEPLIST\" id=\"THSSTYLE2\"><strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">Creation of Self-Signed certificate\n" +
"and Keystore</strong><p>\n" +
"During the initial installation of Tomcat, keystore and self-signed\n" +
"certificate are installed by default.</p>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"A keystore (<tt class=\"file-path\">keystore.jks</tt>) is generated\n" +
"under the directory <tt class=\"file-path\">/eniq/sw/runtime/tomcat/ssl</tt>. This keystore includes the private key and a self-signed certificate.\n" +
"The default password for keystore is stored in <strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">&ldquo;niq.ini&rdquo;</strong> file.</p>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"A self-signed certificate is also exported in a file with extension <tt class=\"file-path\">.cer</tt> under the directory <tt class=\"file-path\">/eniq/sw/runtime/tomcat/ssl/&lt;hostname&gt;.cer</tt></p>\n" +
"</li><li class=\"STEPLIST\" id=\"THSSTYLE2\"><strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">Configuration of Tomcat server.xml\n" +
"To Use the Keystore File</strong><p>\n" +
"To enable HTTPS, Tomcat&rsquo;s <tt class=\"file-path\">server.xml</tt> is configured with following connector using keystore.</p><pre class=\"prencd\">&lt;Connector port=\"8443\" protocol=\"HTTP/1.1\" SSLEnabled=\"true\" maxThreads=\"150\" scheme=\"https\" secure=\"true\" keystoreFile=\"/eniq/sw/runtime/tomcat/ssl/keystore.jks \"keystorePass=<em><strong class=\"HIGHEMPH\">\"&lt;password&gt;\"</strong></em> clientAuth=\"false\" sslProtocol=\"TLS\" /&gt;</pre><p> <strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">where &lt;password&gt; should be replaced with the value given\n" +
"for \"keyStorePassValue\" in /eniq/sw/conf/niq.ini file.</strong></p>\n" +
"</li><li class=\"STEPLIST\" id=\"THSSTYLE2\">In the <tt class=\"LITERALMONO\">&lt;Connector/&gt;</tt> element from\n" +
"the previous step, add <tt class=\"LITERALMONO\">sslEnabledProtocols</tt> parameter\n" +
"as shown below:<pre class=\"prencd\">&lt;Connector port=\"8443\" protocol=\"HTTP/1.1\" SSLEnabled=\"true\" maxThreads=\"150\" scheme=\"https\" secure=\"true\" <strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">sslEnabledProtocols=\"TLSv1.2,TLSv1.1,TLSv1\"</strong> keystoreFile=\"/eniq/sw/runtime/tomcat/ssl/keystore.jks\" keystorePass=<em><strong class=\"HIGHEMPH\">\"&lt;password&gt;\"</strong></em> clientAuth=\"false\" sslProtocol=\"TLS\"/&gt;</pre><p><strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">where &lt;password&gt; should be replaced with the value given\n" +
"for \"keyStorePassValue\" in /eniq/sw/conf/niq.ini file.</strong></p></li><li class=\"STEPLIST\" id=\"THSSTYLE2\"><strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">Restart Apache Tomcat</strong><p>\n" +
"To restart Apache Tomcat, please follow the below steps,</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<ol type=\"a\">\n" +
"\n" +
"<li class=\"substep\">Login as <tt class=\"file-path\">dcuser</tt> on ENIQ server\n" +
"</li>\n" +
"\n" +
"<li class=\"substep\">Run the below command,\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"<tt class=\"input\"><b># webserver restart</b></tt></p>\n" +
"\n" +
"</li>\n" +
"</ol></li></ol>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"Please see <a href='javascript:parent.parent.parent.showAnchor(\"ApacheTomcat1\")' class=\"xref\">Reference [8]</a> for further information.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"\n"+
"</div>\n";

var C4_1_2=
"<div id=\"content\" class=\"body-content\">\n"+
"<h3><span class=\"CHAPNUMBER\">4.1.2 &nbsp; </span><span class=\"CHAPTITLE\"><a name=\"id_s4fu\"></a><a name=\"CHAPTER4.1.2\" href='javascript:parent.parent.sC2(\"TOP\")' class=\"CHAPLINK\">Enabling and Disabling HTTPS</a></span></h3>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"For ENIQ, HTTPS is enabled by default. The status can be changed\n" +
"for each web application using the script <tt class=\"file-path\">change_eniq_security.sh</tt>.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<dl class=\"note\"><dt><b>Note: &nbsp;</b></dt><dd>This script restarts webserver while enabling and disabling\n" +
"the security.</dd></dl><br />\n" +
"\n" +
"<ul>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE0\"><strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">To check whether the status of a\n" +
"module is HTTPS or HTTP.</strong><p>\n" +
"Login to the server as <tt class=\"file-path\">dcuser</tt> and run\n" +
"the below command:</p>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"<tt class=\"input\"><b># cd /eniq/sw/bin/</b></tt></p>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"<tt class=\"input\"><b># bash ./change_eniq_security.sh &lt;<i class=\"var\">web-module-name</i>&gt; status</b></tt></p>\n" +
"</li>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE1\"><strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">To disable HTTPS (switch to HTTP)</strong><p>\n" +
"Login to the server as <tt class=\"file-path\">dcuser</tt> and run\n" +
"the below command:</p>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"<tt class=\"input\"><b># cd /eniq/sw/bin/</b></tt></p>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"<tt class=\"input\"><b># bash ./change_eniq_security.sh &lt;<i class=\"var\">web-module-name</i>&gt; disable</b></tt></p>\n" +
"</li>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE1\"><strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">To enable HTTPS</strong><p>\n" +
"Login to the server as <tt class=\"file-path\">dcuser</tt> and run\n" +
"the below command:</p>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"<tt class=\"input\"><b># cd /eniq/sw/bin/</b></tt></p>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"<tt class=\"input\"><b># bash ./change_eniq_security.sh &lt;<i class=\"var\">web-module-name</i>&gt; enable</b></tt></p>\n" +
"</li></ul>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the above commands, <tt class=\"file-path\">&lt;<i class=\"var\">web_module_name</i>></tt> is the name of the Tomcat application. Below are\n" +
"the valid module names:</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"\n" +
"<ul>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE0\"><tt class=\"file-path\">adminui</tt></li>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE1\"><tt class=\"file-path\">busyhourcfg</tt></li>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE1\"><tt class=\"file-path\">alarmcfg</tt></li>\n" +
"<li class=\"UNORD\" id=\"THSSTYLE1\"><tt class=\"file-path\">universeupdateinstaller</tt></li></ul>\n" +
"\n"+
"</div>\n";

var C4_1_3=
"<div id=\"content\" class=\"body-content\">\n"+
"<h3><span class=\"CHAPNUMBER\">4.1.3 &nbsp; </span><span class=\"CHAPTITLE\"><a name=\"id_8ch1\"></a><a name=\"CHAPTER4.1.3\" href='javascript:parent.parent.sC2(\"TOP\")' class=\"CHAPLINK\">Apace tomcat configuration for\n" +
"Disabling SSLv3.0 and Weak Ciphers</a></span></h3>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"This section describes how to disable SSL3.0 and Configure Medium/Strong\n" +
"ciphers  in Apache Tomcat for ENIQ.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"1.	Open Apache Tomcat <tt class=\"file-path\">server.xml</tt> file<tt class=\"input\"><b> /eniq/sw/runtime/tomcat/conf/server.xml</b></tt></p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"2.	Update Tomcat&rsquo;s server.xml with following connector as\n" +
"shown below and save it:</p><pre class=\"prencd\">&lt;Connector port=\"8443\" protocol=\"HTTP/1.1\" SSLEnabled=\"true\" maxThreads=\"150\" scheme=\"https\" secure=\"true\"<strong class=\"MEDEMPH\"> sslEnabledProtocols=\"TLSv1,TLSv1.1,TLSv1.2\"</strong> keystoreFile=\"/eniq/sw/runtime/tomcat/ssl/keystore.jks\" keystorePass=\"<em><strong class=\"HIGHEMPH\">&lt;password&gt;</strong></em>\" clientAuth=\"false\" sslProtocol=\"TLS\"/&gt;</pre><p><strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">where &lt;password&gt; should be replaced with the value given\n" +
"for \"keyStorePassValue\" in /eniq/sw/conf/niq.ini file.</strong></p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"3. For Cipher configuration, Add the attribute <tt class=\"LITERALMONO\">ciphers=&rdquo;&lt;ciphers list&gt;&ldquo;</tt> in the below connector in server.xml.</p><pre class=\"prencd\">&lt;Connector port=\"8443\" protocol=\"HTTP/1.1\" SSLEnabled=\"true\" maxThreads=\"150\" scheme=\"https\" secure=\"true\" sslEnabledProtocols=\"TLSv1,TLSv1.1,TLSv1.2\" <strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">ciphers=&rdquo;&lt;ciphers list&gt;&ldquo;</strong> keystoreFile=\"/eniq/sw/runtime/tomcat/ssl/keystore.jks\" keystorePass=\"<em><strong class=\"HIGHEMPH\">&lt;password&gt;</strong></em>\" clientAuth=\"false\" sslProtocol=\"TLS\"/&gt;</pre><p><strong class=\"MEDEMPH\">where &lt;password&gt; should be replaced with the value given\n" +
"for \"keyStorePassValue\" in /eniq/sw/conf/niq.ini file.</strong></p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"Use only medium/strong ciphers and avoid using DHE/weak ciphers\n" +
"to overcome vulnerability issues.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<dl class=\"note\"><dt><b>Note: &nbsp;</b></dt><dd>&lt;ciphers list&gt; Please refer <a href='javascript:parent.parent.parent.showAnchor(\"Ciphers\")' class=\"xref\">Reference [12]</a> to\n" +
"get the list of supported ciphers to be provided.</dd></dl><br />\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"4.	Restart Apache Tomcat server. Run the below command as <tt class=\"file-path\">dcuser</tt> user,</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p><tt class=\"input\"><b># webserver restart</b></tt></p>\n" +
"\n" +
"\n"+
"</div>\n";

