"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"This section describes how to export and then import the default\n" +
"self signed certificates to enable Internet Explorer and Chrome to\n" +
"access Eniq Events UI without certification warnings.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
" In the popup <b>Certificate</b> select the <b>Details</b> tab, and click the <b>Copy to File...</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Certificate Export Wizard</b> click the <b>Next&gt;</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Certificate Export Wizard</b> change\n" +
"the format to <b>Cryptograhic Message Syntax Standard - PKCS\n" +
"#7 Certificates (.P7B)</b> then click the <b>Next&gt;</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<div style=\"margin-top: 12pt\"><a name=\"FIGURE12\">[Missing image IE06-cert-export-wizard-format.PNG]</a><p align=\"left\"><i>Figure 12 &nbsp; Certificate Export Wizard</i></p></div>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Certificate Export Wizard</b> in the\n" +
"field <tt class=\"input\"><b>File name:</b></tt> insert <tt class=\"input\"><b>&lt;hostname of the\n" +
"presentation sever&gt;.p7b</b></tt> then click the <b>Next&gt;</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Certificate Export Wizard</b> click the <b>Finish</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the result popup <b>Certificate Export Wizard</b> click\n" +
"the <b>OK</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"Close the open <b>Certificate</b> popup by clicking on\n" +
"the <b>OK</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<dl class=\"note\"><dt><b>Note: &nbsp;</b></dt><dd>For Internet Explorer:<p>\n" +
"In the Internet Explorer browser, click <b>Settings</b> and go to <b>Internet Options</b>.</p>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Internet Options</b> select the <b>Content</b> tab, in the <b>Content</b> tab click the <b>Certificates</b> button.</p>\n" +
"</dd></dl><br />\n" +
"<dl class=\"note\"><dt><b>Note: &nbsp;</b></dt><dd>For Chrome:<p>\n" +
"In the Chrome browser, click <b>Settings</b> and scroll\n" +
"down to the bottom of the screen or until <b>Show advanced settings...</b> is visible.</p>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"Click <b>Show advanced settings...</b> in the expanded\n" +
"section click <b>Manage certificates...</b> button.</p>\n" +
"</dd></dl><br />\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Certificates</b> click the <b>Import...</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Certificate Import Wizard</b> click the <b>Next&gt;</b> button then click the <b>Browse...</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Open</b> change the filetype to <b>PKCS #7 Certificates (*.spc;*.p7b)</b> and browse to the location\n" +
"where the previously exported certificate <tt class=\"input\"><b>&lt;hostname of the\n" +
"presentation sever&gt;.p7b</b></tt> was saved. Select the certificate\n" +
"and click the <b>Open</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Certificate Import Wizard</b> click the <b>Next&gt;</b> button and change the Certificate store: to be <tt class=\"output\">Trusted Root Certification Authorities</tt> by clicking the <b>Browse...</b> button and then click the <b>Next&gt;</b> button</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<div style=\"margin-top: 12pt\"><a name=\"FIGURE13\">[Missing image IE11-cert-import-place.PNG]</a><p align=\"left\"><i>Figure 13 &nbsp; Certificate Import Wizard</i></p></div>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Certificate Export Wizard</b> click the <b>Finish</b> button</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Security Warning</b> click the <b>Yes</b> button. </p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<div style=\"margin-top: 12pt\"><a name=\"FIGURE14\">[Missing image FIG9IE12-security-warning_edited-1.png]</a><p align=\"left\"><i>Figure 14 &nbsp; Security Warning</i></p></div>\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"In the popup <b>Certificate Import Wizard</b> click the <b>OK</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
"Close the popup <b>Certificates</b> by clicking on the <b>Close</b> button, close the popup <b>Internet Options</b> by clicking on the <b>OK</b> button.</p>\n" +
"\n" +
"<p>\n" +
